      "id": "55994d55795f0597",
      "text": "The challenge for the horse/rider system is maintaining the balance which allows us to remain connected. In the moment that my attention wanders it is already lost. The thing that diverts me is always a speck of fear ."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "adebbb971f1d5a5a",
      "text": "The amazing thing I have learnt from horses is about my own **attention** and its links to tension. This is personal mastery of the highest level."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "f1a6532930e7f517",
      "text": "I think that two ingredients are required to put a system on high performance: Power (energy) and Coherence (felt as tension in muscles and/or agitation mentally.) In a horse we call this  \"collection\"."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "42952c28d1abc572",
      "text": "The issue is that power and coherence are interrelated. Too much power can result in loss of coherence. It is best to start with low levels of power and experiment with what more power does to coherence."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "3d3190c344c1fef4",
      "text": "Managing this balance is THE challenge. Put another way, we make haste slowly as I heard Robert Hall say:[[emperors-new-clothes]]."
    },
