      "text": "# What about work?"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "f5ae95826d1a25c9",
      "text": "There is always **effort and work** of course. It is hard physical work looking after horses but good riding should not be so. The rider gets her riding fitness from yard work not from riding! I wrote about this in an article for UK magazine, Horse &  Rider, titled \" How to improve your riding without riding!\" See [[writing-about-equines]]."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
