      "text": "# How do we know we have it?"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "7213e6dfe998dc9c",
      "text": "The competition dressage test is designed to assess the partnership's (organisation's) ability to maintain balance through increasingly difficult transitions ie frequency of changes of direction and pace."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "0a7d7498f946d460",
      "text": "For many this is overwhelming - especially if done \"mechanically\". It cannot be achieved mechanically. When it is there is no beauty (harmony.) There is effort and fatigue. It is the same with our human organisations."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "32c23da1daf7e003",
      "text": "Dressage judges mark the parts. The audience \"marks\" the whole! And sometimes we find it remarkable! The impact of the whole that I am experiencing inspires bliss/wonder/awe. We are all programmed to recognise coherence. It is what we call beauty, vitality or aliveness."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "8d487b33d8103d80",
      "text": "There are signs in the parts when I look at them eg, relaxed ears, glassy relaxed eyes, a softly swishing tail moving in time with the rhythm, fluidity of movement."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "c1068002c7fb9e4c",
      "text": "The horse appears to go into what I call a blank cheque state of pure vulnerability and finds not fear but safety.  Take a look at these videos: [[dressage-tests]].Which of these do you find more beautiful? Why?"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
