    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "cb75146f3ada1bbc",
      "text": "I've realised that I can only [[see auras]] when my system is both powerful and coherent. The instant I stop seeing auras is the instant I have lost my coherence."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "2c04250b2314a3f7",
      "text": "Coherence between two systems is deep connection. Language is superficial and slow. It is a construct - a program that runs our minds. Ironically the more we read the more tied down we become by it. In [[Peter Robertson]]'s terms we are encumbered by feedback and on the 2nd inflexion of the S curve....the death curve."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "512109a5afa486fa",
      "text": "A true mind connection can achieve things much quicker and more safely. We talk of a meeting of minds. We talk of making up our minds about someone really quickly. These are some aspects of this. If we doubt these gifts we will lose them through lack of attention. If we punish these gifts in others we will lose them in humanity."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "67f8832692ef87b9",
      "text": "In the past we maybe lost them due to severe punishment eg burning witches at the stake is likely to stop anyone behaving in a \"witchy\" manner. Ironically many \"witches\" were shopped by other women! Why? Could it be fear of an unseen power."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "da8a8c86d60c3190",
      "text": "Men have more powerful muscles and so can attempt to use force to achieve their aims. Eg I was told to \"make him (my horse) do it\". How? Lean back and use your weight on the rein. Kick him with spurs. Use your whip. It felt awful. If this is riding then I would have given up."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "5335cdf1bb30ff92",
      "text": "There is another way and that is to **give myself up**. When I do this the horse and I become one. It cannot be achieved by high power. We need to restrain the power (hold/contain it) and focus on the rhythm and find a place to do nothing. We have to wait. Then it will come. We can't strive for it or want it. We can't snatch it. It can't be stolen for it is always already there. We can only dis-cover it."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "6076b12e9d1d6b6d",
      "text": "The people who use force believe that the horse is a powerful system to be broken. They fear higher power than theirs. And their response is to break it or discredit it. These same people will \"use\" those on lower power. the two go together. It is action based on envy and greed...Which in turn is based on fear. See [[Implications of Hierarchies]]"
    },
