      "id": "f1a6532930e7f517",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "f1a6532930e7f517",
        "text": "I think that two ingredients are required to put a system on high performance: Power and Coherence (felt as tension in muscles and/or agitation mentally.) In a horse we call this  \"collection\". The issue is that power and coherence are interrelated. Too much power can result in loss of coherence. It is best to start with low levels of power and experiment with what more power does to coherence. Managing this balance is THE challenge. Put another way, we make haste slowly as I heard Robert Hall say:  http://kerry.tries.fed.wiki/view/emperors-new-clothes"
